  "body": "## Use case\r\n\r\nWe have the following file structure:\r\n\r\n```\r\ninterfaces\r\n    IContractA.sol\r\n    IContractB.sol\r\n    index.sol\r\nWorkingContract.sol\r\n```\r\n\r\nand index.sol contains:\r\n```solidity\r\nimport { IContractA } from './IContractA.sol';\r\nimport { IContractB } from './IContractAB.sol';\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the working contract:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// this errors\r\nimport { IContractA, IContractB } from './interfaces';\r\n\r\n// this works\r\nimport { IContractA, IContractB } from './interfaces/index.sol';\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe purpose of putting an index.sol inside a directory could be to remove a lot of imports in working contracts and it looks clean and more readable if one has a lot of contracts/interfaces/libraries they're importing. Very similar to index.js/ts.\r\n\r\nThe feature request is: It'd be great if we could autofill `/index.sol` part if one is importing from a directory.",
